Papers Call for Carrying through Joint Slogans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Papers Sunday editorially say that the joint slogans of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea published in the run-up to the 60th anniversary of the WPK are a militant banner calling upon all the Party members, the whole army and all the people to turn out in an all-out charge to glorify the holiday of October.
 Comprehensively clarified in the joint slogans are the tasks and ways of struggle arising in further strengthening the WPK into the guiding force of the Songun revolution, remarkably increasing the might of the invincible revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu and the might of the single-minded unity, effecting a vigorous revolutionary surge in all fields of the socialist economic construction and speeding up national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says that the WPK made the drumbeat of a new general march for greeting the 60th anniversaries of the WPK and liberation of Korea as a grand festival of victors resound louder by setting forth the militant slogans at an important time when a great leaping progress should be made in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation under the banner of Songun. 
 The joint slogans are the banner of struggle and advance all the Party members, the servicepersons of the People's Army and all the people should hold aloft in the march toward the grand festival of October and a precious guideline and action programme they should apply to their daily work and life, the daily says, calling for holding high the joint slogans to strengthen the single-minded unity of the entire Party, the whole army and all the people around the headquarters of revolution and consolidate the military might of the revolution in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the main task of the present general march to make a decisive turn in economic construction and in improving the standard of people's living this year, which marks the 60th anniversaries of the WPK and the liberation of Korea. We should harvest bumper crops at any cost in this significant year, effect a fresh surge in the fields of electric power, coal and metal industries and railway transport and speed up the revolution in light industry to produce more people's consumer goods of good quality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Party members should take the lead in the struggle to carry through the joint slogans. Officials of all the sectors and all units should arouse the popular masses to new renovations and feats. Youths should fully demonstrate the militant spirit of the young vanguard of Songun in defending the country and building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that as there are the great Party indicating the road ahead of the times and the revolution and the single-minded unity of all the army and people around it, their victory is sure to come in carrying through the joint slogans of the Party.

"Biography of Kim Jong Il" Vol. 2 Published by IIJI 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The International Institute of Juche Idea (IIJI) in Japan published Volume 2 of "Biography of Kim Jong Il" this year, following the publication of Vol. 1 last year.
 The Vol.2 introduces in detail his revolutionary activities and leadership exploits from 1974 to late 1980. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The biography carries a portrait of Kim Jong Il with a bright smile, photos of his making a concluding speech at a national meeting of party information officials, his participating in the 6th Party Congress and his participating in the opening ceremony of the 13th World Festival of Youth and Students and other photos showing his revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Vol.2 consists of 14 chapters (14-27) -- "1974, Year of Change", "For Modeling the Whole Army on the Juche Idea", "Formulation of the Workers' Party of Korea as Mother Party", "For Overall Inheritance and Development of Revolutionary Traditions", "Devotion to the People", "Glorifying President  Kim Il Sung's Revolutionary Exploits", "Single-minded Unity is My Philosophy of Revolution", "Creation of 'Speed of the 80s'", "Noble Compatriotism", "For Independence, Peace and Friendship", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Described in chapters from 14 to 19 are the contents that he was nominated as the successor to the President and led the new historical work of modeling the whole Party and the whole society on the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Edited in chapter from 20 to 24 are his revolutionary activities from the period before the historic 6th Party Congress to late 1980s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Compiled in chapter from 25 to 27 are the leadership exploits he performed for the building of socialist culture, the work of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, national reunification and the accomplishment of the cause of global independence.

U.S. Escape Exercise Disclosed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- It was recently disclosed that the U.S. troops stationed in south Korea have conducted in extreme secrecy the exercises for escaping from the Korean Peninsula to provide for the operations for a preemptive attack upon the north, according to a press report.
 On April 29, the U.S. forces command in south Korea launched an escape exercise to cope with the circumstances of a real war, including the departure of a speed boat carrying the U.S. troops and their families from Pusan Port. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. troops have launched such exercises two times every year in the way of noticing the content of documentary operations for the purpose of rapidly evacuating the U.S. troops and their families in case of emergency on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the U.S. troops conducted the exercise this time under the simulated conditions of an actual war with the participation of the troops and their families in different parts of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such ill-boding military moves meaning the final completion of preparations for a preemptive nuclear attack upon the DPRK clearly hint that the U.S. bellicose forces' ignition of war is just near at hand.

Adherence to Principle of National Independence in Nat�fl Reunification Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The Korean nation's struggle for achieving national reunification is, in essence, the struggle to retake the sovereignty of the nation that was trampled down by foreign forces and realize national independence all over the country. The Korean people's cause of national reunification is a matter of the Korean nation itself and an issue related to the sovereignty of the nation in which any outsider should and can not intervene.
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the principle of national independence is a basic principle of carving out the destiny of the nation all the Koreans should invariably hold fast to and thoroughly apply in the struggle for national reunification, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should hold fast to the principle of national independence that helps achieve the country's reunification with their own efforts as a master according to their independent will and demand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the reunification of the country is to be achieved on the principle of national independence, all the members of the nation should firmly arm themselves with the consciousness of national independence and oppose and reject flunkeyism and the idea of dependence on foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The consciousness of national independence is the ideological might that makes the nation strong and helps all its members fulfill their role as the master of reunification, but flunkeyism and the idea of dependence upon outsiders are an ideological poison that makes a nation servile and impotent and is seriously harmful to reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when all the fellow countrymen have the transparent spirit of national independence and thoroughly reject flunkeyism and dependence on outside forces can the Korean nation accomplish the cause of national reunification in conformity with the will and interests of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To train the stout driving force of the nation is one of important ways to solve the issue of national reunification on the principle of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea and line on the principle of national independence set forth by leader Kim Jong Il is the most just idea and line representing the fundamental interests, demand, unanimous desire and aspiration of the Korean nation. All the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should invariably hold fast to his idea and policy of reunification with national independence and push forward the movement for national independence and reunification, the article concludes.

Pyongyang Mass Rally Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- A Pyongyang mass rally of over 100,000 working people from all walks of life took place at    Kim Il Sung Square Sunday to carry through the joint slogans published by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK.
 Present there were Pak Pong Ju, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop and other senior party and state officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryang Man Gil, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, in a report said that the joint slogans fully reflect the revolutionary aspiration and desire of the Korean people to attain a high goal of building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation as soon as possible under the banner of Songun by brilliantly adorning the 60th anniversary of the WPK with a great victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans set forth the militant tasks and ways for the whole party and army and all the people to achieve a decisive victory in the confrontation with imperialism and the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, united close around leader Kim Jong Il, holding President Kim Il Sung in high esteem for all ages, the reporter said, laying stress on strengthening the single-minded unity of the DPRK in every way with the headquarters of the revolution as its hardcore, holding higher the banner of devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To bring about a decisive turn in the economic construction and people's living this year which marks the 60th anniversaries of the WPK and the national liberation is the main task of the present general advance, the reporter said, calling upon all the party members and other people to turn out as one in the worthwhile struggle to implement the tasks set forth in the joint slogans, glorify the grand October festival with proud victories and create a new heroic epic in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addressing the rally, representatives of all social strata stressed the need to firmly arm all the party members and other working people with the Juche idea and the Songun idea of the WPK, resolutely shatter the imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and actively contribute to consolidating the political and ideological position and class position of the capital as firm as a rock. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers underlined the need to manure and cultivate crops as demanded by the Juche farming method for the present so as to bring about a bumper harvest this significant year in response to the militant appeal of the joint slogan "Let us mobilize all forces to concentrate on farming to hit the target of grain production for this year without fail!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called for creating the construction speed of the Songun era in the construction of the capital as they did the "Pyongyang speed" which startled the world people by marching forward in the saddle of Chollima after the war so as to successfully complete the construction of the assigned objects as scheduled.

RS. Calls for foiling Imperialists' Moves for Ideological and Cultural Poisoning 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The struggle against the imperialists' moves for ideological and cultural poisoning at the present is the struggle to defend the consciousness of national independence and accelerate the building of a new society and, at the same time, the main link of the anti-imperialist struggle, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article.
 Bourgeois ideological and cultural poisoning is a means of aggression and intervention, the article notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the United States has long resorted to the moves for ideological and cultural poisoning through corrupt films, radio voices and television broadcasting, it goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the DPRK is the main target of the U.S. ideological and cultural poisoning. The U.S. enacted the anti-DPRK evil law such as "north Korean Human Rights Act" in spite of opposition and denunciation at home and abroad. It is scheming to divide and disorganize the DPRK and spread American-style "democracy", while planning to nominate a "special envoy in charge of north Korean human rights" under the pretext of "improved human rights". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is now getting all the more vicious in its moves to massively smuggle small radios, ultra-small TV sets, etc. into the DPRK in an attempt to destroy the single-minded unity of the DPRK and disorganize and degenerate it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to shatter the imperialists' moves for ideological and cultural poisoning, it is imperative to enhance the consciousness of national independence and thoroughly reject American-style "democracy" and way of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those countries aspiring after independence should not depend on the "aid" of the West but train their strength in their own spirit and strive to settle the impending issues with their independent and creative stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And they should pay deep attention to ideological education among young people and firmly arm people with anti-American working class consciousness.

Seminar on Famous Work of Kim Il Sung Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- A seminar of workers in the field of education was held at the Grand People's Study House on Friday to mark the 50th anniversary of the publication of President    Kim Il Sung's famous work "On Strengthening the Work of Education and Scientific Research at Colleges and Universities".
 The work, published on July 1, Juche 44(1955), clarifies the importance of training native cadres, the position and role of   Kim Il Sung University in it, the close combination of theoretical education with practice, the issue of educating the students in the spirit of faithfully serving the Party and revolution, the country and people and in the ardent love for the people and the issue of positively conducting scientific researches at colleges and universities to contribute to developing the national economy and promoting the well-being of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers including Song Ja Rip, president of Kim Il Sung University, said that the validity and vitality of the ideas and theories set out in the work have been clearly proven in the educational practice over the last half a century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that leader Kim Jong Il has remained true to the Juche-oriented educational idea of the President, they stressed that under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il a revolutionary change has taken place in the efforts to train the students as revolutionary intellectuals in the Songun era and put the nation's science and technology on a higher level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers called on the officials, teachers and researchers in the educational field to deeply study and grasp the ideas and theories set out in the famous work of the President, explain and prove the greatness of the immortal exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and the Party's Songun politics and successfully solve urgent scientific and technological problems related to the development of the national economy and the improvement of the standard of people's living and thus brilliantly decorate the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and national liberation.
 Present there were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, and Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, and others.

47th Rally for Peace and Disarmament Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- The 47th rally for peace and disarmament was reportedly held in front of the building of the south Korean Ministry of National Defence on June 28 under the sponsorship of the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification.
 Present at the rally were members of civic and public organizations including the Reunification Square, the Association for Supporting Prisoners of Conscience of the Family Movement for Realizing Democracy, the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration and the All-Citizens Measure Committee for the Withdrawal of the Plan for the Deployment of Patriot Missiles and Building of a Citizens' Park on Munhak Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the rally charged that the "mid-term plan for national defence" being pushed forward by the south Korean military authorities under the pretext of "cooperative self-reliant national defence" is aimed to back the realization of strategic flexibility of the U.S. troops in south Korea and introduce high-tech weapons and latest military equipment into south Korea from the United States. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They urged the Ministry of National Defence to fully reexamine the plan designed to stoke confrontation between the south and the north and block peaceful reunification and opt for peace and disarmament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution released at the rally demanded an immediate stop to the military exercises targeted against the north and the arms build-up aimed at escalating the military confrontation and tensions between the south and the north and the drop of spurious "theory of cooperative self-reliant national defence".

Anniversary of Demise of Kim Il Sung Commemorated in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- A lecture, a seminar and a film show were held in Peru and a remembrance meeting in South Africa from June 21 to 26 on the occasion of the 11th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung.
 The first vice-chairman of the National Association of Writers and Artistes of Peru said in the lecture that Kim Il Sung was the only great statesman and leader in history who performed such enormous immortal exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Peruvian-Korean Institute of Culture and Friendship said in the seminar that the immortal feats performed by Kim Il Sung and his deep love for human beings are always remembered not only by the Korean people but by the whole progressive mankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The secretary of the Mfumalanga Provincial Committee of the South African Communist Party who is chairman of the South African Association of Friendship and Solidarity with the Korean People noted at the remembrance meeting that the august name and the feats of the President who dedicated all his life to the human cause of independence would shine for all ages with the history of the struggle of progressive humankind to build a new independent world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a lecture was organized by the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung on June 26.

Information Bulletins Issued in Austria and Nepal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- The Group of Youth for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea in Vienna, Austria, published an information bulletin titled "Kim Il Sung, Immortal Contribution to the Cause of Global Independence" on June 27 on the occasion of the 11th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's demise.
 The bulletin said in an article that Kim Il Sung is not only the father of socialist Korea but the father of independent mankind as he clarified the idea of making the world independent for the first time in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung fathered the Juche idea to be a guiding idea in the era of independence in his early years. He set out the idea and theory of making the whole world independent by applying them to the political field and gave perfect answers to all the theoretical and practical issues arising in advancing the movement for global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung always stood in the van of the struggle for independence in the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set an example in the struggle for national liberation and provided a good precedent in defending sovereignty by defeating the Japanese and U.S. imperialists.
 The tireless efforts made by the President for the growth and development of the non-aligned movement and the exploits performed by him for it occupy a distinguished place in the history of the movement for global independence, the bulletin noted, adding that he led the DPRK to invariably hold aloft the banner of socialism and dynamically steer the socialist movement in the world when Eastern European countries including the former USSR collapsed in the closing years of the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the Nepal-Korea Friendship Association released an information bulletin titled "The Kumsusan Memorial Palace in Korea Is Always Enshrined by the People". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in an article said that the palace is the place where the President lies in state, adding that today many servicepersons and people from all walks of life in the DPRK, overseas compatriots and foreigners visit there to pay highest tribute to him.

Chinese Embassy Officials Labor for Friendship
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- Charge D'affaires Ad Interim Guan Huabing and staff members of the Chinese embassy in Pyongyang did goodwill work at the construction site of the Taean Friendship Glass Factory on July 1, one year after its ground-breaking.
 The guests carried fire-bricks to help the builders in speeding up the final building of a furnace of the smelting workshop. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round different parts of the construction site, being briefed on the factory which is being built as a symbol of the DPRK-China friendship and a monumental edifice thanks to the noble intention of leader Kim Jong Il and President Hu Jintao. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The charge d'affaires ad interim said that he was greatly pleased to see the factory being built well by the close cooperation of technicians under the deep concern of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that he was deeply impressed and encouraged by the devoted work of Korean comrades, he expressed the firm belief that the building of the factory would be completed at an early date to contribute to the Sino-Korean friendship and socialist construction and improvement of the people's living in the DPRK.

Downfall of Capitalism and Victory of Socialism, Law of Historical Development
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- It is an inexorable truth that socialism that is new overpowers and defeats capitalism that is  old and without future, declares Rodong Sinmun Saturday, adding: No force can change this law of historical development.
 The author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In capitalist society, neither the inequality in material life can be removed nor the imbalance between material life and mental and cultural life getting further impoverished and that between the growing demand of the popular masses for independence and their worsening political life can be overcome because the material life of the people becomes deformed, their mental and cultural life impoverished and political life is made extremely reactionary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Herein lie the insoluble contradictions in capitalist society and, for this reason, the collapse of capitalism is inevitable. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Capitalism is in a serious economic crisis and the contradictions and confrontation among the capitalist countries are escalated. Capitalism is the rubbish of history which has lived its days, being the most reactionary old force in human history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stating that socialism is sure to emerge victorious for its scientific accuracy and truth, the article continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism is the ideal of humankind and a society representing its future. The ideal of humankind is to lead an independent and happy life together in a free and peaceful world without any form of exploitation and oppression, domination and subjugation,   aggression and war. This common demand and aspiration of humankind are embodied in socialist idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The orientation of historical development is development to socialism. Transition from capitalism to socialism is the lawful course of the development of human society. If the independence of the popular masses is to be realized, the capitalist society based on individualism has to give place to the socialist society based on collectivism. This is an immovable truth and the historical sum total of the development of human society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world revolutionary people should wage a vigorous struggle to advance the socialist cause, deeply conscious of the scientific truth that it is the law of historical development that capitalism goes to ruin and socialism triumphs.

Centenarians Increase
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- A centenarian birthday table sent by leader Kim Jong Il was conveyed to grandma Song Yong Suk living in Sinyang-dong, Sariwon City, North Hwanghae Province, on Friday.
 Centenarians are growing in number in Korea. This year, too, macrobians have been reported from different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some time ago macrobians including Ko Ok Dok residing in Saegori-dong, Haeju City, South Hwanghae Province, Kim Won Suk in Tohwa-ri, Kaechon City, South Phyongan Province, and Ri Won Ho in Ryonghung-ri, Mundok County, South Phyongan Province, greeted their centenarian birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Old folks who have lived more than 100 years and old men past 90 who have newly registered as macrobians are many across the country. They are under the special care of doctors assigned to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From old times, it was said many people lived long in ideal land with clean air and water. But, before the liberation of the country, the Korean people could not realize their desire to live long in happiness in this good land. In the same land 90-100 years old macrobians are growing in number day by day. This secret cannot be explained only by natural elements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The macrobians say in unison that they live long in good health as they enjoy a happy life under the rays of the sun that has provided them with a kind socialist health care system and takes care of their destiny in a responsible manner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il sends benevolent birthday tables to centenarians, so glad at the reports about them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The increase of macrobians is a pride and joy of the country and they are blessed by the leader. This rare reality can be witnessed only under the socialist system of Korea centred on the popular masses.

Society for Rallying Comrades, First Party Organization in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 2 (KCNA) -- Seventy-five years have elapsed since the first party organization in Korea -- the Society for Rallying Comrades -- was formed.
 After advancing a proper and realistic policy for founding a party at the historic Kalun Meeting (June 30-July 2, 1930) President Kim Il Sung formed the first party organization at Jinmyong School in Kalun on July 3, Juche 19 (1930). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first party organization was the embryo and seed of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
 From then on, the Korean revolution could advance with a true vanguard of revolutionaries of a new generation under the leadership of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a solid foundation for building a party was laid during the hard-fought anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, the WPK could be founded in a matter of two months after the country's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK was further strengthened through the fierce Fatherland Liberation War, the difficult postwar rehabilitation and construction, and the tremendous creation and construction for laying the foundation of socialism through the Chollima upsurge. And it has grown up to be a strong party with millions of members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the trial years of the "Arduous March" and forced march the Party's cohesion and the unity of the revolutionary ranks were cemented. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK, the unity of which has been consolidated thanks to the ideas of the President and the leadership of Kim Jong Il, will always lead the revolution and construction to victory.
